<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-13558] NioEchoServer fails to close resources</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-13558</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;NioEchoServer&lt;/tt&gt; does not close the selectors that it opens. The result of this can be manifested in flaky tests because the JVM/OS can run out of available file descriptors if the &lt;tt&gt;NioEchoServer&lt;/tt&gt; is used in a lot of tests. Each test then leaks a handful of descriptors, and eventually the &apos;too many open files&apos; error is thrown.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was compounded because the &lt;tt&gt;NioEchoServer&lt;/tt&gt; intentionally doesn&apos;t output stack traces, so the underlying issue was hidden and was manifest in odd (flaky) ways in tests.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
